<main class="about-page">
  <div class="about-content-container">
    <h1 class="about-title">About Intersubject</h1>
    <p class="about-subtitle">A practical tool for understanding shared ideas.</p>

    <blockquote class="about-quote">
      “A clear view of how people think—without noise, bias, or performance.”
    </blockquote>

    <h2 class="about-heading">Purpose</h2>
    <p class="about-text">
      Intersubject helps groups see patterns in how people think and agree.  
      It gives educators, teams, and communities a way to turn written opinions into usable insight.
    </p>
    <p class="about-text">
      Instead of profiles or likes, people join text-based cohorts.  
      Each “identify” click adds a data point to a visible map of shared belief.
    </p>

    <h2 class="about-heading">How It Works</h2>
    <h3 class="about-subheading">Identify</h3>
    <p class="about-text">
      Users read a sentence and choose whether they identify with it.  
      Each statement forms a cohort that grows as others agree.
    </p>

    <h3 class="about-subheading">Compare</h3>
    <p class="about-text">
      Overlaps show which ideas attract the same people.  
      The result is a living map of resonance across expressions.
    </p>

    <h3 class="about-subheading">Explore</h3>
    <p class="about-text">
      Users can browse these overlaps to understand trends, values, and viewpoints within any group.
    </p>

    <h2 class="about-heading">Why It’s Different</h2>
    <ul class="about-list">
      <li class="about-list-item"><strong>No profiles:</strong> Ideas, not identities, take center stage.</li>
      <li class="about-list-item"><strong>No algorithmic bias:</strong> Visibility follows participation, not popularity.</li>
      <li class="about-list-item"><strong>No feed:</strong> Interaction is intentional, not endless scrolling.</li>
      <li class="about-list-item"><strong>Transparent data:</strong> Patterns appear directly from user input.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="about-heading">Use Cases</h2>
    <ul class="about-list">
      <li class="about-list-item"><strong>Classrooms:</strong> Gauge student understanding and shared questions.</li>
      <li class="about-list-item"><strong>Teams:</strong> Align culture, values, and goals through quick insight polls.</li>
      <li class="about-list-item"><strong>Coaches & researchers:</strong> Track mindset shifts and interpret qualitative data.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="about-heading">Join In</h2>
    <p class="about-text">
      Each response adds clarity to the map.  
      The more people contribute, the sharper the collective picture becomes.  
      Intersubject grows through participation—one truthful click at a time.
    </p>

    <div class="about-cta-buttons">
      <a href="/auth/register" class="about-cta-button about-primary">Get Started</a>
      <a href="/public" class="about-cta-button about-secondary">Explore Map</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>

